  +card-header('Layout', 'Layouts are ways to control the look and flow of content on the page. #{name} uses flexbox to control the layout of a page where grids are used to control the direction of the layout while cells are used to control the location of the content in the grid.')
  .section
    h2 Grids
    p.
      Grids control the direction of the cells on the page and by default the flow horizontally.
      Grids can contain #[code .cell]'s and they can also contain other #[code .grid]'s.
    pre: code.language-html
      ='<div class="grid">\n'
      ='  <!-- Your cells/grids go here -->\n'
      ='</div>'
  .section
    h2 Cells
    p.
      Cells control the location of a group of content, and range from #[code .cell-1] to #[code .cell-12].
      For multiple cells to fill the width of a grid the sum of the cells should equal 12.
    p(style='white-space:pre;').
      Full Width: #[code .cell-3] + #[code .cell-9] = #[code .cell-12]
      Partial Width: #[code .cell-5] + #[code .cell-5] = #[code .cell-10]
